{
  "texts": [
    "Second, the TCN only convolves the inputs at the present time and previous time since the architecture may accept a time series of any length and map it to output data of the same length.",
    "Dilated convolution.",
    "The dilated convolutions can enable an exponentially large receptive field to ensure the applicability of the causal convolution on sequence tasks (Bai et al. 2018).",
    "For a 1 -D sequence input X ∈ R n and a filter f, the dilated convolution oper- ation on sth element in the sequence X is defined as where d is the dilation factor, k is the filter size, and the subscript X s-d•i denotes the direction of the past.",
    "Therefore, dilation is the same as adding a fixed step after every two consecutive filter taps."
  ]
}